
@startuml

' Classes involved in E-Home-2020 system
class Sensor {
  +vendorId: String
  +description: String
  +unit: Unit
  +roomId: String
  +getLatestValue(): Value
  +getValues(): List<Value>
}

class TemperatureSensor {
  +minValue: float
  +maxValue: float
}

class PowerSensor {
  +totalConsumption: float
}

class Room {
  +roomId: String
  +description: String
}

class Apartment {
  +address: String
  +rooms: List<Room>
  +inhabitants: List<Inhabitant>
  +getEmail(): String
}

class Inhabitant {
  +username: String
  +password: String
  +isAdmin: boolean
  +login(username: String, password: String): boolean
  +setThreshold(sensorId: String, threshold: float): void
  +configureSensor(sensorId: String, newRoomId: String, newDescription: String): void
}

class Value {
  +timestamp: DateTime
  +value: float
}

class SensorController {
  +sensors: Map<String, Sensor>
  +apartments: Map<String, Apartment>
  +addSensor(sensor: Sensor): void
  +registerApartment(apartment: Apartment): void
  +authenticateUser(username: String, password: String): Inhabitant
  +getSensorValue(sensorId: String): Value
}

class EMonitor {
  +checkThresholds(sensorId: String, currentValue: float): boolean
  +sendAlert(email: String, message: String): void
}

' Associations and inheritance
Sensor <|-- TemperatureSensor
Sensor <|-- PowerSensor
Apartment "1" *-- "n" Room
Apartment "1" *-- "n" Inhabitant
SensorController "1" *-- "n" Sensor
SensorController "1" *-- "n" Apartment
Sensor "1" *-- "n" Value
Inhabitant "1" *-- "n" Sensor

' Interfaces (optional)
interface Authenticatable {
  +login(username: String, password: String): boolean
}

Inhabitant --> Authenticatable

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements:
- **Sensor** is the base class with common attributes like `vendorId`, `description`, `unit`, and `roomId`.
- **TemperatureSensor** and **PowerSensor** are derived from **Sensor**, each with their own specific attributes.
- **Room** holds a description and is part of an **Apartment**.
- **Apartment** contains multiple **Rooms** and **Inhabitants**, and has an address.
- **Inhabitant** can log in, set thresholds, and configure sensors if they have admin rights.
- **Value** stores timestamped sensor readings.
- **SensorController** manages all sensors and apartments and handles user authentication.
- **EMonitor** checks thresholds and sends alerts via email if needed.

